            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 1. Origin of the program   </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The issue of human resource management is all the more sensitive today, where the ""digital revolution"" is significantly disrupting working
                    methods, relations between employees and more generally management itself. It is no longer a question of administering but rather of managing
                    the women and men of the company/organisation. The Master in ""Human Resources Management"" pursues precisely this vision.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 2. Obje");
            WriteLiteral(@"ctives of the program </h3>
                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.1. General Objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The Master’s Programme in Human Resources Management (HRM) aims to train managers capable of integrating human resource issues,
                    Operationalize organizational strategies by creating momentum for success through the mobilization and development of the organization’s
                    collective resources.
                    It is aimed at all actors involved in organizational changes, both internally and externally: managers, directors, and expert consultants, faced with
                    situations of change or uncertainty (merger/acquisition, restructuring, relocation, new identity, etc.)
                </p>

                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.2. Specific Objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    <strong> Commmun run to the mention </strong><br/>
          ");
            WriteLiteral(@"          At the end of this program, the students will be able to:
                </p>
                <ul class=""one_list"">
                    <li> 
                        Support organizations in their human resources management challenges;
                    </li>
                    <li> 
                        Ensure regular monitoring of personnel in the various specific projects or missions;
                     </li>
                    <li> 
                        Develop budgets for salary matters;
                    </li>
                    <li> 
                        Control, verify, inspect, critically monitor the management of jobs.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II.3. Program Approach </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The Master in Human Resources Management is aimed at students and professionals from both developing and developed countries who are
                    kee");
